column2: Two windy days prior to sample- S wind- air temp 60
S wind- humid- air temp 85- weeds at surface- yellow lilly pads blooming
Light W wind- air temp 85- lake weeds maturing- rained 1.5" past 2 days.
Partly cloudy- lots of rain last week- only one brood of mallards observed- loons: one pair has 2 young- other pair has 1 young- weeds growing
Partly cloudy- light NW wind- one pair of loons- 2 young diving on own- air temp upper 70's
Occasional clouds- light NW wind- saw second batch of mallard chicks only 3.  Young loons starting to dive- feathers out.  Air temp is 72 degrees- beautiful day.
Partly cloudy- 85 degrees- observed more mallard chicks. Water level up 1"
Partly cloudy- cooler 70 degrees- 4 adult loons together (having dinner at our lake) .  Southwest wind light- rain is predicted.
Partly cloudy- light SW wind observed.  Large gelatinus globs floating.  Loons maturing.
Nice SW wind- partly cloudy- some maples are changing- loons are maturing.
Air temp 83- SW breeze- slow bird activity at feeder and on lake- saw loons feed at noon - mallards must be at nests
Water temp cooling.  Partly cloudy- west wind.  Air temp is 63 degrees.
Have had strong winds- and frequent rain most of the past week.  Cool temps- 40 degrees at night- 60s in the day.  Today is sunny- 66 degrees- water is cooling down- geese are migrating.
Sunny- bright day- upper 60s- west wind.  About 20% color- maples- birch poplar.  Local mallards still here.
Much wind-water very riled up-too cold to swim.
Sighted 3 beavers-east end of lake-one new beaver house this spring.
Heavy winds for 2 days-warm-.  Rain .5 Friday 6/17/94 p.m.  1st time I could not see disc on bottom.  Heavy pine pollen.
Strong E winds- temp. 72.  Mallards are bringing young to feed-3 broods so far of 6-5-8 young.
Lake shows bloom + algae.  Several mallard hatches are feeding.  Baby loon is out feeding with parents.
Lake is cooling-less algae clearer-heavy weed growth-have had frequent rains-now drier.
Lake temp. cooling- young loon growing- shows white crest.
Cooling down.  Very cool nights - 38 degrees F last Thursday.  Some color in maples.
Cool water temp. - very light breeze - 75 degrees air temp.  Clear sky - no rain for several days.
Warm-consistent wind for 3 days-lots of debris-weeds broken off-disturbed.
Little rain last night-hot + muggy today.
Water not clear-brown color-doesn't appear to be algae.
Rain earlier today-turned sunny-clouds building.  Water level: up 3"

Rain on September 26 and September 27. Windy today.
Yesterday it was storming. Today it is misting. High winds.
unusual amount of rain lately. We have a dam that controls the water level.
Sunny. Very windy. White Caps. Excessive amount of rain.
misting and windy. 3 ' rain last night
very warm- no wind and sunny.
cloudy- very windy. A lot of rain recently.
partly cloudy. Light wind. Lots of rain recently.
sunny and calm. Algae evident near shore.
